Gerald,<br><br>
I don't disagree with the general statements that Jeffrey has made.<br><br>
The Lusitania WAS carrying munitions. Secretary of the Navy Franklin D. Roosevelt denied this at the time.<br><br>
As far as the war with Mexico over Texas, did you know that the US was the last country in this hemisphere to abolish slavery? A great war between the states was fought in large part because of the slavery issue. Mexico was dead set against Americans settling in Texas with their slaves.<br><br>
I still have great faith in our country - or more importantly, the American people. Our system of government is the only system that I would wish to live under.<br><br>
But, I think it is important to understand that our leaders are very capable of making bad decisions and even carrying forth terrible policy. Look at MacNamara!<br><br>
Today we have leaders (I use the term loosely) who make mistakes and place themselves above the law. See Al Gore and Bill Clinton.<br><br>
BUT! We have the right to protest, which site #6 is about, and it dates back to the American Revolution. The purpose of protest, whether coming from the right wing or the left, is to hold our leaders feet to the fire and not grant them *carte blanche* in formulating policy.
